{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013i9npACTgL3d4BHBfbDBME","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the changes. The key changes are:\n\n1. Non-success terminal wires now use offset \"link nodes\" (circles) and horizontal lanes below the main graph, instead of the previous approach of just offsetting Bezier curves by a fixed amount.\n2. Wire coloring is now dynamic per result type: green for success results, red for failure results, and a palette of blue/yellow/magenta/cyan/orange for other results.\n3. Per-color arrowhead markers instead of just two (default and fail).\n4. The old \"collector bus\" merge pattern is replaced with the lane-based offset link node approach.\n\nI need to update the design doc at `docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md` to reflect these changes. Let me read the relevant section more carefully.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5354,"cache_read_input_tokens":19095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5354},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fceed27e-6b28-4cf7-a983-d59a4574d900","uuid":"186402f2-e709-49d7-87d4-f6bbe6abd94f"}
