ccess-family results (`succeeded`, `success`, `ok`,\n`done`, `pass`) are green, failure-family results (`failed`, `fail`, `error`) are red,\nand other results cycle through blue, yellow, magenta, cyan, and orange. Each color gets\nits own SVG arrowhead marker.\n\nSuccess wires to terminals draw directly as Bezier curves. Non-success wires to terminals\n(`done` or `abort`) are routed through offset link nodes below the main graph. Each source\nnode drops a vertical line down to a horizontal lane, marked with a colored circle at the\njunction. Wires sharing the same terminal and result name share a lane. The lane connects\nhorizontally and curves up into the terminal node. This keeps failure paths visually\nseparated from the happy path and avoids wire collisions.\n","numLines":18,"startLine":159,"totalLines":235}}}
